node.description:
"Somewhere, in a sparsely populated galaxy, there is a planet like any other. The creatures of this world have four limbs. The two lower limbs enable them to move forward and backward, and the two upper limbs enable them to kill"
This quote is from experimental sci-fi animation masterpiece called ‘Fantastic Planet’ directed by Rène Laloux and based on Stefan's Wul novel. It isn't hard to guess whom this quote is referring to as 'the creatures' with four 'limbs'. It's also easy to understand that Syro 'Drague' Knit is a loving tribute to this very movie. This magnificent blue garment has a loose cropped fit and it is topped with a 3D visualization of the main character inhabiting "Fantastic Planet", called "Drague" as the sweater does.
The meaning of the 'Drague' Knit is based on film's narrative allegory about animal rights and human rights, as well as racism — problems that remain extremely relevant to this day.

node.description: The source of inspiration when creating a skirt is the structural geometry of the natural form - volcanic glass. The folds of the skirt imitate the asymmetrical shape of natural stone, and matte and glossy materials are justified by its heterogeneous texture.

Olska Green (founder of the Ecoolska brand and fashion designer) was inspired by biodiversity of wonderful underwater world. The beauty of nature is the best source of inspiration. Algae plays a significant and integral role in the marine ecosystem. It is very important for balancing marine ecosystems and plays a role in thwarting climate change. You can feel like a mermaid from a fairy tale if you virtually try on this flowing elegant digital dress.

I am looking for inspiration in the real world and I want to reflect its beauty in the virtual world. I wanted to create an unusual dress design and complement it with an interesting texture. I hope I managed to get your attention. thanks!
